The paper proposes a model-based deep reinforcement learning method that combines a learned transition model with rollout simulations to improve data efficiency. This approach is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on deep reinforcement learning and the evaluation on natural language processing tasks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
